<br>
If we say a player or Guild is Evil is that the same as Bad? In my opinion no.<br>
<br>
The Guild Ebon Storm is an evil guild. My understanding is that they are committed to evil. However, the players of that guild conduct themselves with great skill and role play very well. While an Evil guild - I consider them to be good players. However, based on my code I would not group them coz they are &quot;evil&quot; however.<br>
<br>
In contrast I heard of a disasterous experience with Guild X. Also an evil guild. They cheated in a duel I witnessed. Are they bad players? No in my view. Evil character role played well will behave in an evil manner. We should not be surprised if guilds/people dedicated to evil attempt to cheat or cause us harm, even to other players.<br>
<br>
What is Evil? You are not evil because of your race or profession. You are evil if you are committed to doing harm and performing quests that erode your faction with good tribes.<br>
<br>
An evil character is not a bad player.  A bad player role plays poorly or shows little respect or concern for his guild or bretheren. <br>
<br>
So when we consider other guilds or folks and say they are Evil or Bad we mean different things. The former is a roleplaying orientation, while the latter is just a bad player/guild (conduct etc.).<br>
<br>
Is this distinction helpful?  Would you consider this a fair characterization?<br>
<br>
All That is Just!<br>
Exeter<br>
House of Carnage, Officer<br>
